:::summary
The Bible is the foundational scripture of Christianity and Judaism — a library of 66 books (Protestant canon) or 73 books (Catholic canon) spanning thousands of years of God's dealings with mankind. Latter-day Saints revere the Bible as the word of God "as far as it is translated correctly" (Article of Faith 8) and use the King James Version as their standard text. The Bible tells the story of creation, the fall, the covenant with Israel, and the life, death, and resurrection of Jesus Christ.
